 <!-- What does LP6 mean -->
 <section style="padding:3rem 1.5rem;background:var(--color-card-bg);">

 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 What does life path number 6 mean?
 </h2>
 <div class="space-y-4 text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 <p>
 Life path 6 is the Nurturer - the number most fundamentally oriented around care, love, and responsibility to others. Where other numbers are primarily driven by achievement, freedom, or self-expression, LP6 finds its deepest meaning in connection: in being useful to the people they love and in making the environments around them more harmonious and beautiful.
 </p>
 <p>
 In the Pythagorean system, 6 is the number of the home, the family, and the heart. It sits at the center of the number line, balanced between the individual numbers (1–5) and the more collective ones (7–9), and carries something of both: a deeply personal orientation toward love combined with an awareness that love is ultimately something you do for others, not just something you feel.
 </p>
 <p>
 The core challenge for life path 6 is learning that care has to include themselves. LP6's instinct to give is genuine and valuable, but without clear limits, it becomes a pattern that drains the giver and doesn't actually serve the people being given to as well as LP6 believes. The 6 who learns to care for themselves with the same attention they bring to others is a different person. Usually a better one for everyone around them.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Traits image + intro -->
 <section class="py-16 px-4">
 <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
 <div>
 <div class="mb-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden border border-border/60 shadow-lg">
 <img
 src="/images/learn/Life Path Number 6 - Traits.webp"
 alt="Life Path 6 - The Nurturer personality traits"
 class="w-full h-64 object-cover"
 />
 </div>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 Personality traits of life path 6s
 </h2>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
 LP6s are the people others come to with their problems. Not because they've been appointed to the role. They just are. Safety they project, a genuine warmth that doesn't feel performative, that makes people feel they'll be actually heard and not judged. That quality is not something LP6 turns on. It's just how they read.
 </p>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
 They're also highly attuned to beauty and harmony in spaces, in relationships, in how things are arranged. This aesthetic sense runs through everything they touch. An LP6's home tends to feel like a real home. Their presence in a group tends to smooth out the friction. They make things nicer, subtly and consistently, because that's how they see the world.
 </p>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 Underneath the warmth is a well of emotion that LP6 doesn't always surface. They're tenders of others' inner worlds and can be surprisingly private about their own. Getting to the LP6 underneath the nurturer, the person who has fears, needs, and limits, takes time and trust. But it's worth it.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Strengths and challenges -->
 <section style="padding:3rem 1.5rem;background:var(--color-card-bg);">
 <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2" style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
 Strengths &amp; Challenges
 </h2>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)] text-body-text mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
 <span class="text-rpg-green text-xl">✦</span> Core Strengths
 </h3>
